yment  tax  and payroll forms  Please refer to the Employment Forms listed under the HR Forms link on the left side of the webpage for a complete list of the forms  Ensure that you bring the required identification document s  necessary to complete the I 9 Employment Verification Eligibility form  The Human Resources Staff is also available to explain to you about various employment benefits offered and answer any other HR related questions you may have  Please contact VMI s Human Resource Office for any questions regarding in processing  Relocating to Lexington   VMI is a public  four year  undergraduate military college  1 200 students  located in the historic Shenandoah Valley of Virginia  Lexington  population 7 000  also home to Washington   Lee University  offers a stimulating cultural atmosphere  a relaxed rural pace  and a diverse economic base to make life both pleasant and rewarding  The following websites provide information on Lexington and the surrounding area  Lexington Virginia s Visitor Information Lexington Rockbridge Chamber of Commerce Moving   Relocation Expenses Whether you want to rent or own  there are a variety of real estate companies available to help make your transition to Lexington as smooth as possible  When selecting a new residence  be aware that many public utilities  such as sewer and water  are unavailable outside the city limits  Check with your realtor for further information  A directory of the real estate companies registered with the Chamber of Commerce is listed on website above  Please contact your VMI department for questions regarding relocation  We look forward to working with you  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 